7 An Act relating to education; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Section 3-102, which relates to meetings of the State
8 Board of Education; authorizing members to add items
to agendas; providing procedure for adding requested
9 item to an agenda; amending 70 O.S. 2021, Sections 5-
107B and 5-118, which relate to school district
10 boards of education; authorizing members to add items
to agendas; providing procedure for adding requested
11 item to an agenda; and declaring an emergency.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 3-102, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 3-102. A. The State Board of Education shall meet in
18 regular session once each month. Special meetings may be called by
19 the president or by a majority of the members of the Board.
20 B. Upon written request by at least two members of the Board,
21 any member of the Board shall be authorized to place an item on a
22 Board agenda. The item shall be placed on the agenda for the next
23 meeting or a subsequent meeting, as decided by the requesting
24 members, in accordance with the Oklahoma Open Meeting Act.
