1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 5-107B, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 5-107B. A. The board of education of a district with
4 an average daily membership (ADM) of more than thirty thousand
5 (30,000) students may be expanded to add a member who shall be
6 elected at large for a term of four (4) years and who shall serve as
7 chair of the board. The chair of the board position may be added
8 upon a majority vote of the district board of education to add the
9 position. If the board opts to add the chair of the board position,
10 the chair of the board shall be elected at the next regular election
11 of board members, held pursuant to Section 13A-103 of Title 26 of
12 the Oklahoma Statutes, following the decision of the board.
13 B. The chair of the board of education shall possess the same
14 qualifications as required for other board members, shall assume
15 office as provided for other members of the board of education,
16 shall be a full, voting member of the board, and shall count for
17 purposes of a quorum or a majority, or other requirements based on
18 number of members on the board. The chair shall preside at all
19 meetings of the board of education in accordance with rules of
20 parliamentary procedure which have been adopted by a majority vote
21 of the board, provided that, in the absence of rules adopted by the
22 board, the chair shall determine and set forth the rules of
23 parliamentary procedure that shall apply at board meetings; assemble
24 and control the agenda for board meetings, provided that, upon
