1 appr oval of a majority of the members of the board, an item shall be
2 placed on the agenda for the same or a subsequent meeting, in
3 accordance with the Oklahoma Open Meeting Act except as provided by
4 subsection B of Section 5-118 of this title; appoint all committees
5 whose appointment is not otherwise provided for by law; and shall
6 sign all warrants ordered by the board of education to be drawn upon
7 the treasurer for school money. The chair of the board shall
8 possess all powers otherwise provided by law for a member of a board
9 of education, all powers provided by law for the president of a
10 board of education, and such other lawful powers as may be conferred
11 upon the chair by majority vote of the board. The chair shall
12 receive compensation and benefits as conferred upon other members of
13 the district board of education.
14 C. For a district in which a chair of the board has been
15 elected, the district board of education, during the meeting at
16 which the chair of the board assumes office, shall elect a vice-
17 chair who shall serve a one-year term and until a successor is
18 elected and qualified. The vice-chair shall perform all duties of
19 the chair of the board in case of the chair's absence or disability.
20 The board shall also elect clerks and deputies as provided in
21 Section 5-119 of this title. The board shall not elect a president
22 or vice president.
23 D. If a district board of education is expanded to include the
24 chair of the board position, the chair of the board position shall
